To use xrandr
	LIST MONITORS:	xrandr --current
	SET MONITORS:	xrandr --output DP-2 --mode 1920x1080 --scale 1.8x1.8 --below eDP-1
	FIX MONITORS:	xrandr --auto
To use fixm, use the command line arguments:
    -loc/--location:			left-of, right-of, below, above, default right-of
    -scr/--screen/-out/--output:	Name of monitor (xrandr --current), default DP-2
    -sca/--scale:			Dilation factor, default 1.8x1.8
    -res/--resolution/-mod/--mode:	Resolution of monitor, default 1920x1080
